00:22:12.650 --> 00:22:14.940
Jake hurried through the
crowd on Main Street.

00:22:14.940 --> 00:22:17.600
He loosely held a metal
chain in a sweaty right hand.

00:22:17.600 --> 00:22:19.200
Meredith tugged his left.

00:22:19.200 --> 00:22:20.500
"Come with me!"

00:22:20.500 --> 00:22:21.800
she urged him.

00:22:21.800 --> 00:22:23.320
Buildings burned on
either side of them.

00:22:23.320 --> 00:22:26.210
The riots had started a half
hour earlier and this section

00:22:26.210 --> 00:22:29.310
of the city had been
abandoned by authority.

00:22:29.310 --> 00:22:30.610
"How much money is
going to be there?"

00:22:30.610 --> 00:22:31.910
Jake asked.

00:22:31.910 --> 00:22:34.790
"Lots." Meredith stopped
walking, looked sideways at him

00:22:34.790 --> 00:22:37.870
as looters rushed past,
"You getting nervous?"

00:22:37.870 --> 00:22:40.980
He stopped with her and shrugged
trying to come off as nonchalant.

00:22:40.980 --> 00:22:42.280
"I'm good."

00:22:42.280 --> 00:22:43.800
Meredith kept staring.

00:22:43.800 --> 00:22:45.100
"No. I am.

00:22:45.100 --> 00:22:46.680
It's just I should
have brought a shotgun

00:22:46.680 --> 00:22:48.160
or something instead of this chain.

00:22:48.160 --> 00:22:50.760
I'm not really a chain guy."

00:22:50.760 --> 00:22:52.760
"But you're a shotgun guy?"

00:22:52.760 --> 00:22:55.210
"You're saying that like you
don't think I am [laughing]."

00:22:55.210 --> 00:22:57.980
"I don't. I love you, but I don't."

00:22:57.980 --> 00:22:59.340
Meredith started walking again.

00:22:59.340 --> 00:23:00.640
Jake followed her.

00:23:00.640 --> 00:23:03.110
They'd been watching TV in his
tiny apartment when the results

00:23:03.110 --> 00:23:04.700
of the court case had
been announced.

00:23:04.700 --> 00:23:08.210
A white cop who had shot two
black children had been acquitted.

00:23:08.210 --> 00:23:09.650
The shooting had been videotaped

00:23:09.650 --> 00:23:12.580
and the cop had shouted
racial epithets as he fired.

00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:15.760
And right before the trial he'd
had, "I shoot black people,"

00:23:15.760 --> 00:23:17.230
tattooed on his forehead, and,

00:23:17.230 --> 00:23:20.030
"I'm definitely guilty,"
tattooed on his neck.

00:23:20.030 --> 00:23:21.710
But a Grand Jury still
acquitted him.

00:23:21.710 --> 00:23:25.270 position:56%
The city had already been close to
collapse and that pushed it too far,

00:23:25.270 --> 00:23:28.790
broke something inside of
everyone no matter their race.

00:23:28.790 --> 00:23:30.300
The crowd thinned as looters headed

00:23:30.300 --> 00:23:32.590
to the rich stores
where the cops waited.

00:23:32.590 --> 00:23:34.980
Jake followed Meredith
in a different direction

00:23:34.980 --> 00:23:38.020
through side streets until they
reached a small, secluded shop.

00:23:38.020 --> 00:23:41.480
"M&amp;W Musical Instruments?"

00:23:41.480 --> 00:23:42.780
Meredith nodded.

00:23:42.780 --> 00:23:44.080
"This store is loaded.

00:23:44.080 --> 00:23:45.380
Trust me."

00:23:45.380 --> 00:23:47.100
Jake tried the door,
"And it's locked."

00:23:47.100 --> 00:23:49.700
Meredith looked at the long
window facing the street then

00:23:49.700 --> 00:23:51.060
down to his chain.

00:23:51.060 --> 00:23:53.700
"Well, it looks like you
got a key," she smiled.

00:23:53.700 --> 00:23:55.740
And that little smile
sparked something

00:23:55.740 --> 00:23:58.040
in Jake the way it always did.

00:23:58.040 --> 00:23:59.810
It took one swing for
the entire window

00:23:59.810 --> 00:24:02.660
to shatter sprinkle
the ground with glass.

00:24:02.660 --> 00:24:05.370
He hefted the chain in
his hand feeling proud,

00:24:05.370 --> 00:24:08.040
glanced over at Meredith to
see if she was impressed,

00:24:08.040 --> 00:24:11.100
but she was already walking
between rows of instruments.

00:24:11.100 --> 00:24:12.450
"So, where's the safe?"

00:24:12.450 --> 00:24:13.750
"It's in the office."

00:24:13.750 --> 00:24:16.790
Meredith walked slowly like
she was wading through water,

00:24:16.790 --> 00:24:19.330
her fingers traced the
curved wood of a harp.

00:24:19.330 --> 00:24:21.990
"The owner keeps important
stuff out of sight."

00:24:21.990 --> 00:24:23.290
Jake nodded.

00:24:23.290 --> 00:24:24.590
And how do you know him?

00:24:24.590 --> 00:24:25.890
"He's my husband."

00:24:25.890 --> 00:24:27.190
Everything stopped.

00:24:27.190 --> 00:24:28.490
"You're married?"

00:24:28.490 --> 00:24:29.940
"Just a little bit."

00:24:29.940 --> 00:24:31.240
"A little bit?"

00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:32.540
"Jake, it's OK.

00:24:32.540 --> 00:24:33.840
We're going to separate.

00:24:33.840 --> 00:24:35.140
He's not very nice to me."

00:24:35.140 --> 00:24:37.930
"I can't believe this."

00:24:37.930 --> 00:24:40.380
"This store means everything
to him," Meredith said.

00:24:40.380 --> 00:24:42.160
"Let's burn it down."

00:24:42.160 --> 00:24:43.800
"What? Burn it down?"

00:24:43.800 --> 00:24:45.550
"That store across
the street's on fire.

00:24:45.550 --> 00:24:47.010
We can spread it over here."

00:24:47.010 --> 00:24:48.940
"What if someone sees us?"

00:24:48.940 --> 00:24:50.600
Meredith reached into her pocket,

00:24:50.600 --> 00:24:53.060
pulled out a small,
silver hand gun."

00:24:53.060 --> 00:24:54.360
Jake pointed, "That's a gun!

00:24:54.360 --> 00:24:56.770
I didn't know you had a gun!"

00:24:56.770 --> 00:24:59.940
"You seem more upset about
the gun than I'm married."

00:24:59.940 --> 00:25:01.330
"Oh, I'm a democrat."

00:25:01.330 --> 00:25:02.710
Jake rubbed his forehead.

00:25:02.710 --> 00:25:04.440
"Why do you lie to me?"

00:25:04.440 --> 00:25:07.180
Meredith ignored him, walked
deeper into the store.

00:25:07.180 --> 00:25:09.530
"I didn't think we'd be
together forever," Jake lied

00:25:09.530 --> 00:25:11.790
as he followed her, "but
it's been a couple of months.

00:25:11.790 --> 00:25:13.870
How could you not tell
me you're married?"

00:25:13.870 --> 00:25:15.170
Meredith wasn't listening.

00:25:15.170 --> 00:25:17.320
She was staring at
something Jake couldn't see.

00:25:17.320 --> 00:25:21.060
When she spoke again, her voice
was soft and dreamy and distant.

00:25:21.060 --> 00:25:22.480
"He taught me to sing."

00:25:22.480 --> 00:25:26.130
"Who?" Meredith ignored his
question, but it didn't matter.

00:25:26.130 --> 00:25:27.960
Jake knew who.

00:25:27.960 --> 00:25:30.570
"We'd sit in that small room
in the back facing each other

00:25:30.570 --> 00:25:32.430
so close our knees touched.

00:25:32.430 --> 00:25:34.350
When he shut the door,
it was so quiet,

00:25:34.350 --> 00:25:36.780
I felt like we were
buried underground.

00:25:36.780 --> 00:25:40.120
That was before he changed,
before the hitting."

00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:42.070
"Why didn't you tell
me any of this?"

00:25:42.070 --> 00:25:44.100
But her mind was somewhere else.

00:25:44.100 --> 00:25:49.120
Her body in two words, a foot
in each she started to sing.

00:25:49.120 --> 00:25:54.010
&gt;&gt; Sara Jones: You
don't know what love is

00:25:54.010 --> 00:25:59.230
until you've learned the
meaning of the blues,

00:25:59.230 --> 00:26:04.620
until you've loved the
love you've had to lose.

00:26:04.620 --> 00:26:08.110
You don't know what love is.

00:26:08.110 --> 00:26:17.300
You don't know how the lips
hurt until you've kissed and had

00:26:17.300 --> 00:26:22.650
to pay the cost, until
you've flipped your heart

00:26:22.650 --> 00:26:26.060
and you have lost.

00:26:26.060 --> 00:26:31.640
You don't know what
love is [singing].

00:26:31.640 --> 00:26:33.330
&gt;&gt; E.A. Aymar: Jake walked out.

00:26:33.330 --> 00:26:37.220
He stopped and looked back
at Meredith one last time,

00:26:37.220 --> 00:26:39.030
stared at her tall
silhouette in the middle

00:26:39.030 --> 00:26:41.430
of that dark store,
and then he left.

00:26:41.430 --> 00:26:44.490
He walked nearly a mile
dragging his chain behind him

00:26:44.490 --> 00:26:46.580
like a disappointed snake.

00:26:46.580 --> 00:26:48.650
Meredith had always
seemed unattainable to him,

00:26:48.650 --> 00:26:51.550
but there is something about
that distance that drew him.

00:26:51.550 --> 00:26:52.850
No. Not the distance.

00:26:52.850 --> 00:26:54.250
The moments it was absent.

00:26:54.250 --> 00:26:57.990
The surprising moments when she
turned toward Jake completely his,

00:26:57.990 --> 00:26:59.870
carefree and excited.

00:26:59.870 --> 00:27:01.860
Walking away from her was unreal.

00:27:01.860 --> 00:27:05.380
It made his insides feel like
a box of loose puzzle pieces.

00:27:05.380 --> 00:27:07.670
And then he heard her singing.

00:27:07.670 --> 00:27:14.180
&gt;&gt; Sara Jones: You don't know
how hearts burn for a love

00:27:14.180 --> 00:27:19.210
that cannot live yet never dies,

00:27:19.210 --> 00:27:24.300
until you've faced its
dawn with sleepless eyes.

00:27:24.300 --> 00:27:31.550
You don't know what love is.

00:27:31.550 --> 00:27:34.070
&gt;&gt; E.A. Aymar: It was impossible.

00:27:34.070 --> 00:27:36.190
He was a mile away and
the night wasn't quiet.

00:27:36.190 --> 00:27:41.110
There were shouts from Main Street,
sirens, the low roar of fire.

00:27:41.110 --> 00:27:44.490
Jake turned and followed the sound
all the way back to the shop.

00:27:44.490 --> 00:27:48.410
He stood in the shadows and stared
inside, stared at Meredith's body

00:27:48.410 --> 00:27:51.240
on the ground and a man
kneeling next to her.

00:27:51.240 --> 00:27:54.410
Jake recognized him from a
photo he'd seen on her phone.

00:27:54.410 --> 00:27:55.710
"Who's that?"

00:27:55.710 --> 00:27:57.010
he'd asked.

00:27:57.010 --> 00:27:58.400 position:56%
"Oh." Meredith had replied, "No one.

00:27:58.400 --> 00:28:00.090
Some guy named Will."

00:28:00.090 --> 00:28:02.800
Now will rose to his feet
and Jake stepped back deeper

00:28:02.800 --> 00:28:04.110
into the shadows.

00:28:04.110 --> 00:28:06.890
The nearby fire warmed him,
cast enough light for him

00:28:06.890 --> 00:28:10.010
to see Will walk over to a wall
and rest his head against it,

00:28:10.010 --> 00:28:12.290
and to see the gun Will held.

00:28:12.290 --> 00:28:14.090
Jake hadn't realized
he was inside the store

00:28:14.090 --> 00:28:16.290
until the glass cracked underfoot.

00:28:16.290 --> 00:28:18.750
He knelt next to Meredith,
turned her over,

00:28:18.750 --> 00:28:21.750
saw the hole where
her face used to be.

00:28:21.750 --> 00:28:23.830
"She was trying to
burn my store down."

00:28:23.830 --> 00:28:26.520
Will pointed to a burning
two by four in the corner.

00:28:26.520 --> 00:28:27.840
"I saw her carrying that.

00:28:27.840 --> 00:28:30.180
She was trying to burn
my store down."

00:28:30.180 --> 00:28:33.110
Jake wasn't aware that he was
wrapping the chain around his fist.

00:28:33.110 --> 00:28:36.470 position:56%
He barley understood he was standing
or that he'd thrown a punch,

00:28:36.470 --> 00:28:38.390
not until an ache from
the chain reverberated

00:28:38.390 --> 00:28:40.470
up his arm and Will fell back.

00:28:40.470 --> 00:28:43.100
Will looked for the gun, but
it had flown out of his hand.

00:28:43.100 --> 00:28:45.710
Jake punched him again
this time across the jaw.

00:28:45.710 --> 00:28:49.090
Will hit the floor hard,
uncontrolled, unconscious.

00:28:49.090 --> 00:28:52.890
Jake enrolled the chain from
his fist and picked up the gun.

00:28:52.890 --> 00:28:55.480
He perched his foot on
the other man's chest,

00:28:55.480 --> 00:29:00.770
aimed the gun at his head, "this is
for Meredith," he said, and fired.

00:29:00.770 --> 00:29:03.440
The bullet exploded
into his own foot.

00:29:03.440 --> 00:29:05.700
Jake cried out and fell
down grabbing his ankle,

00:29:05.700 --> 00:29:07.360
