00:32:36.410 --> 00:32:41.870 position:56%
And, as usually what happens to Kit,
she happens to find a dead body.

00:32:41.870 --> 00:32:44.640
So this is the point in the
story in which, you know,

00:32:44.640 --> 00:32:46.170
the mystery really gets started.

00:32:46.170 --> 00:32:51.360
Without a moment's hesitation,
I sprung to the man's side.

00:32:51.360 --> 00:32:54.400
The face was contorted,
but I still recognized him.

00:32:54.400 --> 00:32:58.610
It was Grayson Bancroft dressed in
the same suit he'd worn to dinner.

00:32:58.610 --> 00:33:01.820
Obviously, Grayson never
made it to bed last night.

00:33:01.820 --> 00:33:05.600
His skin was extremely
pale, not a good sign.

00:33:05.600 --> 00:33:08.390
Tentatively, I reached
to feel for a pulse.

00:33:08.390 --> 00:33:12.600
After grasping his stone cold
hand for only a second I recoiled.

00:33:12.600 --> 00:33:15.850
The president of the
Mayflower Society was dead.

00:33:15.850 --> 00:33:17.550
Now, it was time to panic.

00:33:17.550 --> 00:33:20.270
The eerie silence consuming the
entire building prevented me

00:33:20.270 --> 00:33:21.760
of lending out a scream.

00:33:21.760 --> 00:33:25.140 position:56%
Instead, I scrambled around the
corner and flew down the last flight

00:33:25.140 --> 00:33:27.530
of stairs to reach
the main entrance.

00:33:27.530 --> 00:33:29.730
The concierge desk sat empty.

00:33:29.730 --> 00:33:31.290
Didn't anyone start the day early

00:33:31.290 --> 00:33:34.150
in Washington even at
the Continental Club?

00:33:34.150 --> 00:33:37.930
The delicious aroma of freshly
baked rolls wafted in my direction.

00:33:37.930 --> 00:33:40.440
Of course the Continental
Club was a prime location

00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:42.480
for a beltway power breakfast.

00:33:42.480 --> 00:33:44.830
I followed my nose, which
led me to the entrance

00:33:44.830 --> 00:33:46.490
of the garden dining room.

00:33:46.490 --> 00:33:49.460
Two well-dressed businessmen
were waiting to be seated.

00:33:49.460 --> 00:33:50.760
"Could someone help me?"

00:33:50.760 --> 00:33:53.840
I asked. My black capris
running pants, a hoodie,

00:33:53.840 --> 00:33:56.640
and yellow tennis shoes
didn't inspire confidence.

00:33:56.640 --> 00:33:59.600
The club's host took one look
at me and wrinkled his nose.

00:33:59.600 --> 00:34:01.220
"I'll be with you in
a moment, ma'am.

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:03.450
As soon as seat these
two gentlemen."

00:34:03.450 --> 00:34:06.400
Given the circumstances,
waiting was out of the question.

00:34:06.400 --> 00:34:07.700
"Sir, I'm sorry.

00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:09.280
But I need your assistance now!"

00:34:09.280 --> 00:34:12.310
My voice was only a
decibels shy of a scream.

00:34:12.310 --> 00:34:13.850
I'd gotten his attention.

00:34:13.850 --> 00:34:16.350
"Please. I have to ask
you to wait your turn."

00:34:16.350 --> 00:34:19.210
The two men in suits shook
their heads in disgust.

00:34:19.210 --> 00:34:20.510
He left me no choice.

00:34:20.510 --> 00:34:23.790
I hadn't wanted to spoil
breakfast for the eager diners.

00:34:23.790 --> 00:34:25.440
"There's a dead man upstairs.

00:34:25.440 --> 00:34:27.250
He's inside the library."

00:34:27.250 --> 00:34:28.550
That did it.

00:34:28.550 --> 00:34:30.500
All three men stared
at me mouths agape.

00:34:30.500 --> 00:34:33.450
Given their reactions, I might as
well have announced the arrival

00:34:33.450 --> 00:34:35.290
of Queen Elizabeth's corpse.

00:34:35.290 --> 00:34:38.160
The host stammered,
"What did you say?"

00:34:38.160 --> 00:34:42.500
I cleared my throat and spoke in my
clearest, most sophisticated voice,

00:34:42.500 --> 00:34:44.550
"His name is Grayson Bancroft.

00:34:44.550 --> 00:34:47.350
I don't know what happened to
him, but someone might want

00:34:47.350 --> 00:34:48.980
to attend to the matter."

00:34:48.980 --> 00:34:51.130
I turned on my heels and retreated.

00:34:51.130 --> 00:34:53.800
The club staffer followed
behind apparently deciding

00:34:53.800 --> 00:34:56.360
that the two guests were
no longer a priority.

00:34:56.360 --> 00:34:59.510
When he caught up with me, he
put his hand on my shoulder.

00:34:59.510 --> 00:35:00.810
"Can you show me..."

00:35:00.810 --> 00:35:02.110
and his voice trailed off.

00:35:02.110 --> 00:35:03.410
I turned to face him.

00:35:03.410 --> 00:35:04.710
"The body?"

00:35:04.710 --> 00:35:06.010
He gulped.

00:35:06.010 --> 00:35:07.310
"Yes." "Follow me."

00:35:07.310 --> 00:35:08.610
I motioned toward the stairs.

00:35:08.610 --> 00:35:11.110
Once we reached the first floor
landing we continued past the

00:35:11.110 --> 00:35:13.550
portrait and reached
Franklin's statue.

00:35:13.550 --> 00:35:16.190
I pointed in the direction
of the library entrance.

00:35:16.190 --> 00:35:19.800
Fortunately, although not for
Grayson, the body remained

00:35:19.800 --> 00:35:21.850
in exactly the same spot.

00:35:21.850 --> 00:35:24.440
"He's the leader of the Historical
Society group we're hosting

00:35:24.440 --> 00:35:26.830
for the next three
days," the host said.

00:35:26.830 --> 00:35:30.170
Despite my best efforts, I
couldn't hide my exasperation.

00:35:30.170 --> 00:35:32.610
"That's what I was
trying to tell you."

00:35:32.610 --> 00:35:34.540
He knelt down besides Bancroft.

00:35:34.540 --> 00:35:36.480
"Are you sure he's dead?"

00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:39.180
"I'm no medical examiner,
but his hand is cold

00:35:39.180 --> 00:35:41.010
and I can't detect a pulse.

00:35:41.010 --> 00:35:42.610
And he's not breathing.

00:35:42.610 --> 00:35:45.830 position:56%
If you could stay here, I'm going to
call an ambulance and the police."

00:35:45.830 --> 00:35:48.630
I nodded. If I'd had my phone
I could have texted Doug

00:35:48.630 --> 00:35:50.880
until the alerts on
his device woke him.

00:35:50.880 --> 00:35:54.030
My best laid plans for a jog
this morning had gone awry.

00:35:54.030 --> 00:35:56.530
I squatted next to the
body for a closer look.

00:35:56.530 --> 00:35:58.410
The twisted features
definitely belonged

00:35:58.410 --> 00:36:00.220
to the man I met the night before,

00:36:00.220 --> 00:36:02.850
enough to make a positive
identification.

00:36:02.850 --> 00:36:06.540
Unfortunately, Bancroft
didn't seem to be at peace.

00:36:06.540 --> 00:36:08.890
Grayson had been in
relatively good shape.

00:36:08.890 --> 00:36:10.190
His weight appeared average

00:36:10.190 --> 00:36:13.520
and he was likely a few years
shy of Medicare eligibility.

00:36:13.520 --> 00:36:15.800
If he suffered from an
illness like cancer,

00:36:15.800 --> 00:36:19.070
the effects of such a serious
disease certainly weren't apparent.

00:36:19.070 --> 00:36:20.480
Was it a heart attack?

00:36:20.480 --> 00:36:21.780
Perhaps he smoked.

00:36:21.780 --> 00:36:23.220
I got closer to his
face and sniffed.

00:36:23.220 --> 00:36:26.700
I was particularly sensitive
to the smell of cigarettes.

00:36:26.700 --> 00:36:30.060
Although I detected the lingering
fragrance of a men's cologne,

00:36:30.060 --> 00:36:32.190
there was no hint of tobacco.

00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:34.410
Something seemed odd about
the placement of the body.

00:36:34.410 --> 00:36:37.480
If he'd been a victim of cardiac
arrest, wouldn't he have fallen

00:36:37.480 --> 00:36:39.210
to the ground in a crumpled heap?

00:36:39.210 --> 00:36:42.040
Instead, Bancroft was lying
perfectly flat on his back,

00:36:42.040 --> 00:36:44.130
arms and legs spread wide.

00:36:44.130 --> 00:36:46.160
It was as though he'd
been in the middle

00:36:46.160 --> 00:36:48.890
of making a snow angel
when he'd died.

00:36:48.890 --> 00:36:50.940
I returned to the library
and bent down again.

00:36:50.940 --> 00:36:54.020
The expression on his face
seemed frozen like something

00:36:54.020 --> 00:36:57.600
out of the ordinary had happened to
him and he'd been unable to react.

00:36:57.600 --> 00:36:59.580
There was no other
way to describe it.

00:36:59.580 --> 00:37:03.130
Grayson Bancroft had
been surprised to die.

00:37:03.130 --> 00:37:04.910
When staring at the
expression of shock

00:37:04.910 --> 00:37:06.940
on Bancroft's face
I noted the small,

00:37:06.940 --> 00:37:08.570
red mark on the dead man's neck.

00:37:08.570 --> 00:37:11.390
It was on the left side
inches above the fitted collar

00:37:11.390 --> 00:37:13.230
of his buttoned down dress shirt.

00:37:13.230 --> 00:37:15.920
It was quite noticeable and I was
almost certain it hadn't been there

00:37:15.920 --> 00:37:17.220
the night before.

00:37:17.220 --> 00:37:20.700
Leaning over the body, I moved
closer for a better look.

00:37:20.700 --> 00:37:23.080
It wasn't a birth mark
or a mosquito bite.

00:37:23.080 --> 00:37:26.480
To my untrained eye, it
appeared to be a puncture wound.

00:37:26.480 --> 00:37:28.020
"Who are you and what
are you doing?"

00:37:28.020 --> 00:37:31.450 position:56%
I drew back immediately at the sound
of an authoritative female voice.

00:37:31.450 --> 00:37:34.590
A petite woman whipped
out a badge and flashed.

00:37:34.590 --> 00:37:37.860
"Detective Maggie Glass,
DC Metro Police."

00:37:37.860 --> 00:37:40.870
I stood up and offered her
my hand, "Kit Marshall.

00:37:40.870 --> 00:37:42.440
I discovered the body."

00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:45.380
The detective was joined
by several EMTs.

00:37:45.380 --> 00:37:47.330
Their visit would be brief
because I was certain

00:37:47.330 --> 00:37:49.790
that Grayson Bancroft was deceased.

00:37:49.790 --> 00:37:52.660
I moved away while the emergency
medical personnel surrounded the

00:37:52.660 --> 00:37:54.420
body and confirmed the death.

00:37:54.420 --> 00:37:57.390
Glass motioned for me
to exit the library.

00:37:57.390 --> 00:37:59.640
The middle-aged detective
was short in stature,

00:37:59.640 --> 00:38:01.500 position:56%
but I could tell she meant business.

00:38:01.500 --> 00:38:03.450
Her brown hair was
pulled back in a ponytail

00:38:03.450 --> 00:38:06.580
and she wore a fitted black
suit that was professional,

00:38:06.580 --> 00:38:09.910
yet also sporty in case a
hot pursuit was called for.

00:38:09.910 --> 00:38:12.660
Silver button earrings
provided a feminine touch.

00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:13.960
She pulled out a notebook

00:38:13.960 --> 00:38:16.040
and grabbed a pen from
her jacket pocket.

00:38:16.040 --> 00:38:19.010
"Miss Marshall, you're a guest
here at the Continental Club?"

00:38:19.010 --> 00:38:22.010
I briefly described the reason for
our visit and explained I lived

00:38:22.010 --> 00:38:24.700
in Washington, D.C.
metropolitan area.

00:38:24.700 --> 00:38:26.000
"Where do you work?"

00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:29.180
Apparently the district police
ask this question as an opener.

00:38:29.180 --> 00:38:32.760
Maybe they also attended too
many K Street cocktail parties.

00:38:32.760 --> 00:38:34.060
"Capitol Hill.

00:38:34.060 --> 00:38:35.360
I work for a chief
of staff for a member

00:38:35.360 --> 00:38:37.160
of the House of Representatives."

00:38:37.160 --> 00:38:38.460
"A political type I see.

00:38:38.460 --> 00:38:39.760
No surprises there.

00:38:39.760 --> 00:38:41.910
How did you come to
discover the deceased?"

00:38:41.910 --> 00:38:44.340
MY workout attire corroborated
my story

00:38:44.340 --> 00:38:48.040
and Glass didn't question why
I stumbled across Grayson.

00:38:48.040 --> 00:38:50.720
She continued to write
furiously in her notebook.

00:38:50.720 --> 00:38:52.400
Without looking up,
she kept talking.

00:38:52.400 --> 00:38:54.260
"Only a few more questions,
Miss Marshall.

00:38:54.260 --> 00:38:55.760
This seems open and shut.

00:38:55.760 --> 00:38:57.490
The coroner will take it from here.

00:38:57.490 --> 00:39:00.060
It was most likely a heart
attack or an aneurysm.

00:39:00.060 --> 00:39:03.540
We see these all the time and
men of the deceased's age group."

00:39:03.540 --> 00:39:04.840
I cleared my throat.

00:39:04.840 --> 00:39:06.140
That got Glass's attention.

00:39:06.140 --> 00:39:09.360
She glanced up from scribbling
furiously in her notepad and asked,

00:39:09.360 --> 00:39:11.840
"Do you have something to add?"

00:39:11.840 --> 00:39:13.870
"Detective, I'm sure you
noticed the odd position

00:39:13.870 --> 00:39:15.590
of the body on the floor."

00:39:15.590 --> 00:39:16.890
"Not really.

00:39:16.890 --> 00:39:18.540
I wanted to let our medical
experts confirm the death.

00:39:18.540 --> 00:39:19.970
Let's take another look."

00:39:19.970 --> 00:39:21.270
She motioned with the pen

00:39:21.270 --> 00:39:23.320
that I should follow
her inside the library.

00:39:23.320 --> 00:39:26.900 position:56%
Glass circled the body several times
and paused to write in her notebook.

00:39:26.900 --> 00:39:29.090
She indicated the medics
should join us.

00:39:29.090 --> 00:39:30.720
"Fellas, does this look
like a heart attack

00:39:30.720 --> 00:39:32.580
or an otherwise natural
death to you?"

00:39:32.580 --> 00:39:35.560
The younger guy shook
his head, "Seems weird.

00:39:35.560 --> 00:39:38.090
Like he hit the ground
and just froze."

00:39:38.090 --> 00:39:40.100
The other EMT rubbed his chin,

00:39:40.100 --> 00:39:42.200
"Can't see I've seen anything
like this in real life.

00:39:42.200 --> 00:39:45.390
It reminds me of something
I saw on cable TV."

00:39:45.390 --> 00:39:46.690
"What do you mean?"

00:39:46.690 --> 00:39:47.990
I asked. "You know.

00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:49.910
One of those channels with
the historical documentaries.

00:39:49.910 --> 00:39:51.210
It's like that town in Italy

00:39:51.210 --> 00:39:53.850
where the volcano erupted
thousands of years ago."

00:39:53.850 --> 00:39:55.150
"Pompeii?"

00:39:55.150 --> 00:39:56.450
I offered.

00:39:56.450 --> 00:39:57.810
He raised a triumphant
finger, "You've got it!

00:39:57.810 --> 00:40:00.720
Everyone was killed and then
preserved instantly by ash.

00:40:00.720 --> 00:40:03.830
This guy looks like one of those
unlucky people stopped dead

00:40:03.830 --> 00:40:05.130
in his tracks."

00:40:05.130 --> 00:40:08.440
Glass stared at the paramedic for
a long moment before speaking.

00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:09.740
"Well, one thing's for certain.

00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:12.120
There was no volcano in the
middle of the Continental Club.

00:40:12.120 --> 00:40:13.430
So what killed him?"

00:40:13.430 --> 00:40:15.910
The detective bent down
to take a closer look.

00:40:15.910 --> 00:40:18.910 position:56%
She immediately noticed the red mark
on the dead man's neck and motioned

00:40:18.910 --> 00:40:21.570
for the History Channel
watching medic to join her.

00:40:21.570 --> 00:40:22.870
"What do you see here?

00:40:22.870 --> 00:40:24.170
Is it a wound?

00:40:24.170 --> 00:40:25.470
A bug bite?"

00:40:25.470 --> 00:40:27.110
The paramedic hesitated
almost as if to say

00:40:27.110 --> 00:40:30.630 position:56%
that answering her question exceeded
his pay grade, but he complied

00:40:30.630 --> 00:40:33.010
without protest even
whipping out a small pen light

00:40:33.010 --> 00:40:35.050
to shine on Bancroft's neck.

00:40:35.050 --> 00:40:37.710
"I'm not a medical examiner,
ma'am, but that's not

00:40:37.710 --> 00:40:39.860
from a mosquito," he concluded.

00:40:39.860 --> 00:40:42.890
Glass grabbed the pen light
and peered at the small blotch.

00:40:42.890 --> 00:40:44.740
"That's helpful, but what is it?"

00:40:44.740 --> 00:40:46.310
"Maybe an injection site.

00:40:46.310 --> 00:40:47.700
You can see the dot in the center.

00:40:47.700 --> 00:40:49.400
There's a bit of blood around it."

00:40:49.400 --> 00:40:52.450
Detective glass must have agreed
with the medic's conclusion.

00:40:52.450 --> 00:40:55.590
After examining Grayson's neck
again she leaned back and said,

00:40:55.590 --> 00:40:57.090
"Thank you for your help.

00:40:57.090 --> 00:40:59.780
Everything had happened so fast
I hadn't had much time to think

00:40:59.780 --> 00:41:02.660
about the consequences of
finding the mysterious mark

00:41:02.660 --> 00:41:05.840
on Bancroft's body, an
odd and inauspicious start

00:41:05.840 --> 00:41:09.670
to my morning had suddenly turned
into something more sinister.

00:41:09.670 --> 00:41:11.530
Detective Glass jotted
down more notes

00:41:11.530 --> 00:41:13.400
and tapped her pen to her forehead.

00:41:13.400 --> 00:41:16.100
To no one in particular
she stated the obvious,

00:41:16.100 --> 00:41:18.350
"I don't like how this
is shaping up."

00:41:18.350 --> 00:41:19.650
I drew nearer.

00:41:19.650 --> 00:41:21.730
"Detective, I'm clearly not
going for a run this morning.

00:41:21.730 --> 00:41:25.200
Do you mind if I return to my
room so I can speak with my fiance

00:41:25.200 --> 00:41:27.430
and put on more appropriate
clothes?"

00:41:27.430 --> 00:41:31.320 position:56%
With an absentminded sideways
glance, Glass answered, "Of course."

00:41:31.320 --> 00:41:35.020
Then, she quickly added, "Don't
go anywhere else, Miss Marshall.

00:41:35.020 --> 00:41:37.930
You may have just become a
key witness to a murder."

00:41:37.930 --> 00:41:41.140
I was no stranger to
those fateful words.

00:41:41.140 --> 00:41:42.940
Thank you.

