00:52:07.310 --> 00:52:10.980
I stepped up to her judging
table to set down my pie.

00:52:10.980 --> 00:52:14.580
"Same kind as last year," Ivy said
with a small shake of her head.

00:52:14.580 --> 00:52:17.500
"I love mincemeat pie,
especially near to the holidays."

00:52:17.500 --> 00:52:19.260
I smiled again.

00:52:19.260 --> 00:52:21.090 position:56%
"Well, good luck to you then, Sissy.

00:52:21.090 --> 00:52:23.560
This might finally be your year."

00:52:23.560 --> 00:52:25.300
Sissy. She was always calling me

00:52:25.300 --> 00:52:28.170
that even though she knew
damn well I was married now

00:52:28.170 --> 00:52:32.130
and should be called Mrs. Cecilia
Burns if she wanted to be proper.

00:52:32.130 --> 00:52:34.510
Ivy's eyes opened wide and
she fussed at her orange,

00:52:34.510 --> 00:52:36.870
polka dotted scarf when
she saw Jean Brodie walking

00:52:36.870 --> 00:52:40.190
up with a lattice topped
deep dish apple.

00:52:40.190 --> 00:52:42.930
She just about toppled her chair
over backwards jerking up like

00:52:42.930 --> 00:52:45.950
that from her seat reaching
across the table to take the pie

00:52:45.950 --> 00:52:49.220
from Jean acting all
friendly and whatnot.

00:52:49.220 --> 00:52:54.220
I heard Ivy call Jean a
dirty bitch -- b-word --

00:52:54.220 --> 00:52:56.770
once in the bathroom
back in school just

00:52:56.770 --> 00:52:59.790
because her daddy owned the
junk yard and repair shop.

00:52:59.790 --> 00:53:01.090
Ivy didn't know I heard her.

00:53:01.090 --> 00:53:03.450
I had my feet propped up on
the toilet like I used to do

00:53:03.450 --> 00:53:04.800
so I could hear what
those girls were saying

00:53:04.800 --> 00:53:07.010 position:56%
when they thought no one was around.

00:53:07.010 --> 00:53:09.870
I guess Ivy thinks Jean's all right
now since she's rick on account

00:53:09.870 --> 00:53:13.650
of her husband owning the one
and only car dealership in town.

00:53:13.650 --> 00:53:16.310
Owned. It's Jean's now.

00:53:16.310 --> 00:53:20.020 position:56%
Her husband fell over one day on the
lot a year or so back right in front

00:53:20.020 --> 00:53:21.720
of a couple he'd just
taken for a test drive

00:53:21.720 --> 00:53:24.130
in a brand new Buick Riviera.

00:53:24.130 --> 00:53:26.860
I heard he clutched his chest
and called out for Jean.

00:53:26.860 --> 00:53:29.620
He was romantic like that.

00:53:29.620 --> 00:53:31.900
"Jean, you just have to come
up to our next fundraiser,"

00:53:31.900 --> 00:53:34.270
Ivy said through her smile,
still tugging at her scarf

00:53:34.270 --> 00:53:36.320
in that anxious way of hers.

00:53:36.320 --> 00:53:39.900
"We're raising money to buy a new
nativity scene for the square."

00:53:39.900 --> 00:53:41.740
"So I've heard," said Jean.

00:53:41.740 --> 00:53:43.040
She folded her hands in front

00:53:43.040 --> 00:53:45.770
of her showing off her
expensive leather gloves.

00:53:45.770 --> 00:53:48.190
"I like your scarf," I interrupted.

00:53:48.190 --> 00:53:50.020
Jean and Ivy both looked at me.

00:53:50.020 --> 00:53:53.370
Ivy smirked and tilted her
head, then turned back to Jean.

00:53:53.370 --> 00:53:56.980
Jean squinted at me like I had
a toe growing between my eyes.

00:53:56.980 --> 00:53:58.280
"Like I was saying.

00:53:58.280 --> 00:54:01.940 position:56%
The little Christ baby from our old
nativity, the paint's all worn away.

00:54:01.940 --> 00:54:04.680
It's not right having him sit out
there all chip-faced and decrepit.

00:54:04.680 --> 00:54:07.160
It goes against God."

00:54:07.160 --> 00:54:08.980
"How are you doing, Cecilia?"

00:54:08.980 --> 00:54:11.440
Jean Brodie asked me a question.

00:54:11.440 --> 00:54:12.740
"Fine, thanks.

00:54:12.740 --> 00:54:14.040
And you?" "I'm all right.

00:54:14.040 --> 00:54:15.720
And how is Mr. Burns?"

00:54:15.720 --> 00:54:18.370
I beamed and reached up a
hand to straighten my hat.

00:54:18.370 --> 00:54:19.670
"We're both just fine.

00:54:19.670 --> 00:54:20.970
Thanks for asking."

00:54:20.970 --> 00:54:22.460
"Glad to hear it," Jean said.

00:54:22.460 --> 00:54:24.550
"I do see your husband from
time to time always out

00:54:24.550 --> 00:54:26.220
and about in his tow truck.

00:54:26.220 --> 00:54:29.700
Sometimes he pulls old trade-ins
to the lot that don't run anymore."

00:54:29.700 --> 00:54:32.890 position:56%
"Oh, he's on the road all the time,"
I said tripping over my words.

00:54:32.890 --> 00:54:34.370
"We'd have two or three
babies by now

00:54:34.370 --> 00:54:36.290
if he could just be
home more often."

00:54:36.290 --> 00:54:38.500
"Yes. I'm sure that's
true," Jean said wistfully.

00:54:38.500 --> 00:54:41.130
"Just remember, life's little
blessings come along right

00:54:41.130 --> 00:54:42.970
when they're supposed to."

00:54:42.970 --> 00:54:45.030
I nodded and smiled
like I always do.

00:54:45.030 --> 00:54:46.890
The children at the next
table rubbed sticky paint

00:54:46.890 --> 00:54:49.230
onto maple leaves and pressed
them onto construction paper.

00:54:49.230 --> 00:54:53.220
"I just remembered," Jean said
acting all surprised, "Ivy,

00:54:53.220 --> 00:54:54.890
weren't you and Marvin
king and queen

00:54:54.890 --> 00:54:57.060
of the Fall Fest back in the day?"

00:54:57.060 --> 00:54:59.850
"Oh, yes, we were," Ivy said acting
like she couldn't quite remember.

00:54:59.850 --> 00:55:01.830
"But that was so long ago."

00:55:01.830 --> 00:55:03.780
"Yes, I suppose we've
all gotten a lot older.

00:55:03.780 --> 00:55:07.730 position:56%
Well, you ladies enjoy the seasons,"
Jean said in her grand way.

00:55:07.730 --> 00:55:10.910
She waved to someone in
the crowd and drifted off.

00:55:10.910 --> 00:55:12.280
I turned back to Ivy.

00:55:12.280 --> 00:55:15.730
Her eyes burned into the
back of Jean's cashmere coat.

00:55:15.730 --> 00:55:18.520
She had that same look on her
face that she did back in school,

00:55:18.520 --> 00:55:22.250
but this time she was too afraid
to call Jean a b-word out loud

00:55:22.250 --> 00:55:25.400
in public not that
we were all grownups.

00:55:25.400 --> 00:55:27.900
A surprise bubble of laughter
rolled up my chest and I coughed

00:55:27.900 --> 00:55:29.200
into my fist to keep it down.

00:55:29.200 --> 00:55:32.520
I sat on a cold, metal folding
chair and watched the rest

00:55:32.520 --> 00:55:34.370
of the fall fest pies come in.

00:55:34.370 --> 00:55:35.670
I knew mine was different.

00:55:35.670 --> 00:55:38.830
It would be the one they'd
all be talking about after.

00:55:38.830 --> 00:55:41.130
When it came time for judging,
Ivy and her friends hovered

00:55:41.130 --> 00:55:42.960
over the gingham tablecloth
all official

00:55:42.960 --> 00:55:44.980
and whatnot in their frilly aprons.

00:55:44.980 --> 00:55:48.050
They tasted little bits of pie
from their plastic forks acting

00:55:48.050 --> 00:55:51.140
out for all of us like they didn't
ever take big bites of anything.

00:55:51.140 --> 00:55:53.560
Then, they joked about getting
fat and watching their waistlines

00:55:53.560 --> 00:55:56.840
like judging a pie contest was the
last thing they wanted to be doing.

00:55:56.840 --> 00:55:59.830
I watched especially close
when Ivy tasted mine.

00:55:59.830 --> 00:56:02.750
I pressed my own hand
to my narrow side.

00:56:02.750 --> 00:56:05.250
It was almost done hurting
from that last time.

00:56:05.250 --> 00:56:08.170 position:56%
Marvin was good about leaving the
marks under my clothes so when I was

00:56:08.170 --> 00:56:11.040
out and about in town no one
could see my black and blues.

00:56:11.040 --> 00:56:14.100
I could keep my head up and look
at everyone in the eye that way.

00:56:14.100 --> 00:56:17.040
I slipped my hand into my pocket
and felt the folded piece of paper,

00:56:17.040 --> 00:56:20.290 position:56%
smoothed edges from all those times
I had folded it and refolded it ever

00:56:20.290 --> 00:56:22.000
since I found it last
week on laundry day.

00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:24.210
"We have a winner!"

00:56:24.210 --> 00:56:25.510
Ivy shouted.

00:56:25.510 --> 00:56:29.190 position:56%
She stuck the big blue ribbon on the
table in front of Jean's apple pie.

00:56:29.190 --> 00:56:30.490
Some people tried to clap

00:56:30.490 --> 00:56:33.580 position:56%
