flimsy cups of cider in their hands.

00:56:33.580 --> 00:56:35.710
They sounded like that hurt
bird I found in the yard

00:56:35.710 --> 00:56:37.690
that time flapping its
wings for no reason just

00:56:37.690 --> 00:56:39.220
because it thought it should.

00:56:39.220 --> 00:56:41.940
I knew that bird would
never fly again.

00:56:41.940 --> 00:56:43.240
Jean made her way to the table

00:56:43.240 --> 00:56:46.820
and took a flowery bow thanking
all the judges one by one.

00:56:46.820 --> 00:56:49.580
She took an extra-long time
thanking Ivy holding both her hands

00:56:49.580 --> 00:56:51.430
with her own and pumping
them up and down.

00:56:51.430 --> 00:56:52.730
They looked like a couple

00:56:52.730 --> 00:56:55.170
of overdressed milk maids
churning a pot of butter.

00:56:55.170 --> 00:56:57.660
Then, Jean turned and smiled right
at me before she wandered off

00:56:57.660 --> 00:56:58.960
in the crowd ribbon in hand.

00:56:58.960 --> 00:57:03.410
I heard a few sirens that night,
but they were too far off for me

00:57:03.410 --> 00:57:04.710
to place what part of town.

00:57:04.710 --> 00:57:07.070
I was in my usual chair
at the kitchen table,

00:57:07.070 --> 00:57:10.130
the radio playing John
Coltrane low from the counter.

00:57:10.130 --> 00:57:11.500 position:56%
Marvin didn't have a taste for music

00:57:11.500 --> 00:57:12.880
that he said white
people had nothing to do

00:57:12.880 --> 00:57:15.220
with so I always kept an
eye out for the headlights

00:57:15.220 --> 00:57:18.390
so I can turn it off quick just to
keep him from shouting about it.

00:57:18.390 --> 00:57:22.980
I ate my pie slowly, one bite of
minced meat and a bite of apple,

00:57:22.980 --> 00:57:25.510
