straight across,

01:19:13.430 --> 01:19:16.070
but the end near her feet
was drawn tightly together

01:19:16.070 --> 01:19:18.380
as if it had been tied with a rope.

01:19:18.380 --> 01:19:22.250
She could not possibly untie
something knotted on the outside.

01:19:22.250 --> 01:19:25.660
The only way out would be
to tear the straight edge.

01:19:25.660 --> 01:19:28.590
Perveen searched through
her small, beaded purse,

01:19:28.590 --> 01:19:33.280
which contained a few coins,
business cards, the vile of attar,

01:19:33.280 --> 01:19:36.780
and her mother of pearl
fountain pain.

01:19:36.780 --> 01:19:40.410
She removed a metal hairpin from
her braided coronet and tried

01:19:40.410 --> 01:19:42.460
to stab it through the cloth.

01:19:42.460 --> 01:19:45.820
The thin pin broke
on the 5th attempt,

01:19:45.820 --> 01:19:49.000
but she really needed
a sharp bit of metal.

01:19:49.000 --> 01:19:53.160
She thought of the whale
bones inside her brassiere,

01:19:53.160 --> 01:19:57.810
but she didn't have enough space to
move her arms to unhook her blouse.

01:19:57.810 --> 01:20:00.080
So she took the fountain
pen and rubbed its nib

01:20:00.080 --> 01:20:01.850
against the sharp, broken hairpin.

01:20:01.850 --> 01:20:04.900
It took only a few
minutes of industrious work

01:20:04.900 --> 01:20:07.760
to give the pen's nib
a knife-like sharpness.

01:20:07.760 --> 01:20:09.830
She was elated when
she pushed the pen

01:20:09.830 --> 01:20:12.650
into the bag's fabric
and it went through.

01:20:12.650 --> 01:20:14.530
Diligently, she stabbed the cloth

01:20:14.530 --> 01:20:17.330
until she made an opening
of a few inches.

01:20:17.330 --> 01:20:21.360
Then, with her hands, she tore
it open the rest of the way.

01:20:21.360 --> 01:20:24.530
Squeezing herself out, she
slowly released her arms and legs

01:20:24.530 --> 01:20:26.560
from the tight ball they'd been in.

01:20:26.560 --> 01:20:30.050
Her right foot throbbed with
pain and so did some spots

01:20:30.050 --> 01:20:32.230
in her back and one elbow.

01:20:32.230 --> 01:20:34.580
But she was free.

01:20:34.580 --> 01:20:38.640
In a short, dark space
that smelled of dust.

01:20:38.640 --> 01:20:42.990
Groping around, she identified
many more sacks around her.

01:20:42.990 --> 01:20:45.930
The crowding gave the
impression she was in a storeroom,

01:20:45.930 --> 01:20:50.020
perhaps one of the many go-downs
built in rows near the harbor

01:20:50.020 --> 01:20:52.870
or at Ballard Pier itself.

01:20:52.870 --> 01:20:57.000
Goods were held for months and
sometimes years in the go-downs.

01:20:57.000 --> 01:21:00.360
She remembered her brother Rustam's
frustration about a shipload

01:21:00.360 --> 01:21:04.100
of nails that should have been
delivered to Mistry Construction,

01:21:04.100 --> 01:21:09.270 position:56%
but had been accidently stored after
the unloading and forever lost.

01:21:09.270 --> 01:21:11.550
She tried to think logically.

01:21:11.550 --> 01:21:13.310
She'd been loaded into this place.

01:21:13.310 --> 01:21:15.940
There had to be a way
to the outside.

01:21:15.940 --> 01:21:20.090
First, she searched the low ceiling
hoping to find the base of a shoot.

01:21:20.090 --> 01:21:23.180
There was none, at
least not near her.

01:21:23.180 --> 01:21:27.970 position:56%
She shifted her investigation to the
cold cement walls around the sacks.

01:21:27.970 --> 01:21:32.650 position:56%
Moving made her feel the impact of
begin in a windowless, doorless box.

01:21:32.650 --> 01:21:35.930
She was becoming frightened,
realized that not knowing

01:21:35.930 --> 01:21:38.140
where she was in relation
to the bag she'd broken

01:21:38.140 --> 01:21:40.640
out of made her feel lost.

01:21:40.640 --> 01:21:45.400
Perveen said a silent prayer and
afterward her mind felt clear.

01:21:45.400 --> 01:21:48.180
If she'd been brought to a
place already filled with goods,

01:21:48.180 --> 01:21:51.100
she'd probably been left close
to the front of the space

01:21:51.100 --> 01:21:53.040
and whatever door existed.

01:21:53.040 --> 01:21:56.770
She crawled back to the spot
where the destroyed bag lay.

01:21:56.770 --> 01:21:58.940
Then she sat down and
felt everything around it.

01:21:58.940 --> 01:22:03.080
A raised edge on the wooden
base caught her attention.

01:22:03.080 --> 01:22:05.920
When she touched it, she
realized it was one edge

01:22:05.920 --> 01:22:08.150
of a large wooden square.

01:22:08.150 --> 01:22:11.990 position:56%
She was able to pry up the square
and pushed one of her hands through.

01:22:11.990 --> 01:22:15.400
Her initial confusion was
followed by the realization

01:22:15.400 --> 01:22:19.780
that she'd been loaded
up onto a shelf.

01:22:19.780 --> 01:22:23.570
This was the reason for the
very low ceiling above her head.

01:22:23.570 --> 01:22:26.970
The way out was to drop down
to the next level, though,

01:22:26.970 --> 01:22:31.920
how steep the fall would be and
what she'd land on was unknown.

01:22:31.920 --> 01:22:36.320
Sometimes people kept guard
dogs in the storerooms.

01:22:36.320 --> 01:22:40.110
There were even rumors of
certain merchants keeping snakes,

01:22:40.110 --> 01:22:43.170
which would dissuade
both thieves and rats.

01:22:43.170 --> 01:22:45.800
She whistled to see if
a dog might move below,

01:22:45.800 --> 01:22:48.800
but there was no sound in response.

01:22:48.800 --> 01:22:50.680
Perveen slowly fit herself

01:22:50.680 --> 01:22:54.000
through the opening feeling
her way down with her feet.

01:22:54.000 --> 01:22:56.760
But then her tired arms
couldn't hold her anymore.

01:22:56.760 --> 01:22:59.700
She slipped straight down
landing in a sitting position

01:22:59.700 --> 01:23:01.980
on another group of sacks.

01:23:01.980 --> 01:23:05.690 position:56%
She sat there for a while making
sure no bones were broken, although,

01:23:05.690 --> 01:23:08.080
when she gathered the
strength to stand,

01:23:08.080 --> 01:23:10.690
she had a searing pain in her hip.

01:23:10.690 --> 01:23:13.610
Resolutely, she bumped her way
around the room to the area

01:23:13.610 --> 01:23:16.950
where she saw some
thin streaks of light.

01:23:16.950 --> 01:23:19.120
A ventilated wooden
door, she decided,

01:23:19.120 --> 01:23:21.620 position:56%
after exploring it with her fingers.

01:23:21.620 --> 01:23:24.390
Unfortunately, it was locked.

01:23:24.390 --> 01:23:26.470
Pressing her eyes to the
narrow bits of light,

01:23:26.470 --> 01:23:29.520
she realized the door was
near an area with people.

01:23:29.520 --> 01:23:32.370
She heard the rumble of
men's voices and, again,

01:23:32.370 --> 01:23:34.810
the blowing of a ship's horn.

01:23:34.810 --> 01:23:38.050
She must be at the
harbor very close by.

01:23:38.050 --> 01:23:39.350
She could hear voices.

01:23:39.350 --> 01:23:42.680
That also meant someone
might hear her.

01:23:42.680 --> 01:23:43.980
"Help me!"

01:23:43.980 --> 01:23:46.090
she called in English
and then in Marathi.

01:23:46.090 --> 01:23:49.950
She shouted again and
again, but nobody heard.

01:23:49.950 --> 01:23:54.180
Perhaps it was still too early
or the storeroom too distant.

01:23:54.180 --> 01:23:57.190
Starting around seven,
the dock became lively,

01:23:57.190 --> 01:24:01.020
but then there might be too much
noise for a tiny cry to be heard.

01:24:01.020 --> 01:24:03.840
She had to draw attention
to the door in hopes

01:24:03.840 --> 01:24:07.410
that the earliest workers,
the tea makers, the sweepers,

01:24:07.410 --> 01:24:09.950
and the stock loaders might hear.

01:24:09.950 --> 01:24:12.390
Perveen put her hand in her purse.

01:24:12.390 --> 01:24:14.330
She could write a note
and push it through one

01:24:14.330 --> 01:24:17.240
of the ventilation holes,
but the laborers reporting

01:24:17.240 --> 01:24:19.340
to work were all illiterate.

01:24:19.340 --> 01:24:23.130
Then she felt the cool glass
of the vile of rose attar.

01:24:23.130 --> 01:24:27.370
If she spilled it, she'd
create an overpowering aroma.

01:24:27.370 --> 01:24:30.330
An expensive feminine
scent that was unusual

01:24:30.330 --> 01:24:33.720
for the dock might draw men
to the storeroom's door.

01:24:33.720 --> 01:24:36.470
If she could push the
ana and pisa corns

01:24:36.470 --> 01:24:40.840
through the ventilation holes
they might catch someone's eye.

01:24:40.840 --> 01:24:45.570 position:56%
Perveen opened the vile and spilled
it along the open edges of the door.

01:24:45.570 --> 01:24:48.450
Then, she pushed an ana
through hearing it clink

01:24:48.450 --> 01:24:51.520
as it hit cobblestones outside.

01:24:51.520 --> 01:24:52.820
"Take the money!"

01:24:52.820 --> 01:24:56.050
she bellowed feeling like
a huckster at the circus.

01:24:56.050 --> 01:24:58.550
"Money! Money!

01:24:58.550 --> 01:25:01.510
Money!" Thanks.

01:25:01.510 --> 01:25:14.120
